A pre-mortem imagines the project has already failed, then works backwards to understand why — before it happens. Run one before each significant sprint or feature.

Use `/sdlc-premortem` to facilitate a structured pre-mortem session. Results from each session are appended here.

---

## How to use this document

1. Run `/sdlc-premortem` at the start of a sprint or before a significant feature.
2. Work through the failure imagination exercise.
3. Score risks (likelihood × impact).
4. Commit to mitigating the top 3 risks.
5. Add top risks to `.sdlc/risk-register.md`.
6. Append this session below.

